                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jernigan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby.</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-20">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 20, 1894</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Alleged Japanese spies arrested on French concession by French police, at
                    instance of China. Delivered at this consulate by French consul-general.
                    Disclaimed the right to exercise Japanese consular functions. Accused asked for
                    asylum till case could be investigated. Granted, with understanding that I
                    retain power to preserve status quo. They and papers secure; advise patience;
                    important principle involved. Reasonable doubt China’s rights. No danger of
                    prejudice. Assure Yamên of my strict impartiality and my purpose to maintain
                    status quo. Have written fully.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jernigan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
